00:14:20.772 --> 00:14:21.102
Sorry.

236
00:14:22.432 --> 00:14:22.442
Hi.

237
00:14:23.272 --> 00:14:26.672
I was wondering what immune cells you think are playing a role

238
00:14:27.452 --> 00:14:30.492
in the results that you showed on the last slide.

239
00:14:30.912 --> 00:14:34.272
That's a great question. Unfortunately, I can't answer that.

240
00:14:34.592 --> 00:14:38.412
We are working on that now, but if you want, I can

241
00:14:38.472 --> 00:14:41.812
update you about that because we are doing that experiment now.

242
00:14:44.632 --> 00:14:45.652
I have a quick question.

243
00:14:46.472 --> 00:14:49.632
So do you think there's something specific about this mechanism in the lung?

244
00:14:50.332 --> 00:14:52.952
Or have you tested this in other metastatic sites?

245
00:14:54.132 --> 00:14:57.512
So lung is here important because of breast cancer

246
00:14:57.552 --> 00:14:58.732
metastasis, but

247
00:14:59.532 --> 00:15:03.192
the importance of this is after cancer

248
00:15:03.232 --> 00:15:06.752
therapies like radiation, they're locally on the tumor

249
00:15:06.872 --> 00:15:10.461
tissues, on the primary tumor. But some cells can

250
00:15:10.492 --> 00:15:14.172
